## Web Research Complete

**Queries**: 6 searches executed
**Sources**: 10 relevant sources found (6 web + 4 local design assets)
**Artifact**: `/home/asiri/.archon/workspaces/alexsiri7/reli/artifacts/runs/4b93754fc2b02134bf78bbb3c089dd38/web-research.md`

### Key Findings

- **No new CSS or tokens needed** — `index.css` already has `.glass`, `.no-scrollbar`, `.safe-area-pb`, and all design tokens. Use existing utilities + Tailwind classes directly.
- **Bottom nav changes (App.tsx)**: Add `backdrop-blur-xl bg-canvas/80 border-t border-white/5` glassmorphism, `h-20` tab height, and active dot indicator via CSS `after:` pseudo-element on active tab button.
- **Active icon distinction**: Design uses Material Symbols with fill variant — project uses SVG icons. Simplest fix is a filled SVG path per tab for the active state (pattern already in the codebase).
- **Hero card (Sidebar.tsx)**: On mobile, the "The One Thing" card needs `p-8`, `text-3xl font-black`, gradient glow overlay (`bg-gradient-to-br from-primary-container to-primary blur-xl opacity-20`).
- **Chat context pills**: Horizontal `overflow-x-auto no-scrollbar flex gap-2` with `whitespace-nowrap rounded-full` pills — `no-scrollbar` class already in `index.css`.
- **Briefing "Good Morning"**: Display heading + bento-grid sweep findings (`grid-cols-2`) + stats row at bottom.
- **All mobile changes must be gated with `md:` breakpoints** — desktop layout must not change.

### Gaps

- `rounded-full` in design HTML maps to `0.75rem` (their custom config), but in the project's Tailwind v4 it's `9999px`. Use `rounded-xl` or `rounded-2xl` for cards where the design says `rounded-full`.

Sources:
- [Creating Glassmorphism Effects with Tailwind CSS | Epic Web Dev](https://www.epicweb.dev/tips/creating-glassmorphism-effects-with-tailwind-css)
- [Tailwind CSS backdrop-filter blur](https://tailwindcss.com/docs/backdrop-filter-blur)
- [Understanding env() Safe Area Insets in CSS](https://medium.com/@developerr.ayush/understanding-env-safe-area-insets-in-css-from-basics-to-react-and-tailwind-a0b65811a8ab)
- [scroll-snap-type - Tailwind CSS](https://tailwindcss.com/docs/scroll-snap-type)
- [Make Your PWAs Look Handsome on iOS](https://dev.to/karmasakshi/make-your-pwas-look-handsome-on-ios-1o08)
